Abdomen: Segments I–VII each with 2 pairs of sa 2 and sa 3 tufts of long black truncate, cylindrical setae and segment VIII with 1 pair of tufts of similar long black setae, each abdominal setal tuft consisting of 8–18 setae surrounding single, long, black primary seta (
Fig. 36 b
